China Potash Output May Rise to 6 Million Tons in 2011: Industry Chairman

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-10-16T03:12:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-10-16/china-potash-output-may-rise-to-6-million-tons-in-2011-industry-chairman.html
China ’s potash output may rise to 6
million tons this year, Wei Chengguang, the chairman of the
Chinese potash industry association, said today at a conference
in  Shanghai .  China’s investment overseas and in domestic mines will
result in 13.5 million tons of new capacity a year by 2015, and
the global potash market will face overcapacity in 2012-2014,
Wei said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
